</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Overhead Press Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Place a barbell at about chest height.</li>



<li>Grip the bar wider than shoulder width and step close to it.</li>



<li>Inhale and raise the bar so it is resting on your collarbone.</li>



<li>Press the bar up until your arms are straight while exhaling.</li>



<li>Inhale at the top and lower the bar carefully to your shoulders.</li>



<li>Repeat.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a strong and stable stance with your feet hip-width apart.</li>



<li>Keep your core and glutes engaged throughout the exercise.</li>



<li>Steer clear of using momentum or bouncing the weight to help lift it overhead.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



