</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Incline Dumbbell Bench Press Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the incline of your bench to around 30-45 degrees.</li>



<li>Sit down and lift a pair of dumbbells.</li>



<li>Press the dumbbells from the starting position to up to straight arms while exhaling.</li>



<li>Inhale while lowering the dumbbells to your shoulders.</li>



<li>Repeat.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a neutral spine position by engaging your core and avoiding excessive arching.</li>



<li>Start with a manageable weight and focus on maintaining proper form and control.</li>



<li>Maintain a strong and steady grip on the dumbbells throughout the exercise.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



